'''Lowndes Academy''' is an independent school in [[Lowndesboro, Alabama]], founded in 1966 as a segregation academy.  

==History==
Lowndes academy was founded in 1970 as a segregation academy.<ref>{{cite news|title=Private white academies struggle in changing world|publisher=Birmingham News|author=Carla Crowder|date=October 27, 2002|url=http://www.al.com/specialreport/birminghamnews/index.ssf?blackbelt/blackbelt16.html|accessdate=January 6, 2013}}</ref>

==Accreditation==
Lowndes Academy is accredited by the [[Alabama Independent School Association]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://0101.nccdn.net/1_5/3db/33e/00d/Directory-12-13.pdf|publisher=AISA|title=AISA directory|accessdate=January 6, 2013}}</ref>

